	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Im an agnostic High Elf enchanter Level 8, and this is how i did it.  Hehe. and I only died once!<BR>
<BR>
I used Illuision: Gnome and was dubious to all guards.  Make sure you put on Invis before zoning because Illusion will drop when you zone.  Reapply Illusion after you show up so if Invis times out you aren't dead meat.  :)  Make sure there isnt any guards nearby!<BR>
<BR>
When you enter, you will be in the foreign quarter.  The zone to Neriak Commons is due south.  In Neriak commons head south till you are over the bridge, turn left (east).  The tunnel to Neriak 3rd gate is nearby on the east wall.  Once in 3rd gate, Keep going east till you hit a courtyard type of area with guards patroling there.  Take the second door from the left.  You can see the library steps from the doorway. the person who sells the enchant metal spells is on the first floor.  CAUTION... DO NOT go around the building!!  the necro and SK guild is back there guarded by Ghouls!  they can see through Invis, and dont like Gnomes.. once they started attacking me, I ran, and the guards joined in. :(<BR>
<BR>
Once i bought my spells i just gated out.<BR>
<BR>
Over all it was quite exciting sneeking into a hostile city for spells that will make me money in the future.  At least i took enough money to purchase enchant silver, electrum, and gold.  So I wont have to come back for a long time.. :)
				</font>
			</td>

